    relatedPosts: [],
    content: "# How to Set Up Online Ordering for Your Restaurant in 2026\n\nOnline food delivery now accounts for **35% of restaurant revenue** in India ŌĆö and it's growing at 20% per year. If your restaurant isn't set up for online ordering, you're missing a third of your potential revenue.\n\nBut there's a catch: Zomato and Swiggy take 18-25% commission on every order. On Ōé╣10 lakh monthly delivery revenue, that's Ōé╣1.8-2.5 lakh going to aggregators every month. The smart approach is to use aggregators for discovery while building your own direct ordering channel.\n\nHere's how to set up both.\n\n## Option 1: Zomato and Swiggy (Aggregators)\n\n### Commission Breakdown\n\n| Platform | Base Commission | Packaging Fee | Payment Gateway | Effective Rate |\n|----------|----------------|---------------|-----------------|----------------|\n| Zomato | 18-22% | Ōé╣5-15/order | 2% | 20-25% |\n| Swiggy | 18-22% | Ōé╣5-15/order | 2% | 20-25% |\n| Dunzo | 15-18% | Ōé╣5/order | 1.5% | 17-20% |\n\n**What you actually receive:**\nOn a Ōé╣300 order with 22% commission:\n- Order value: Ōé╣300\n- Commission (22%): -Ōé╣66\n- Packaging fee: -Ōé╣10\n- Payment gateway (2%): -Ōé╣6\n- **You receive: Ōé╣218** (72.7% of order value)\n\n### How to Set Up on Zomato\n\n1. Visit partner.zomato.com and click \"Add Your Restaurant\"\n2. Enter restaurant details (name, address, cuisine type)\n3. Upload menu with photos and prices\n4. Submit documents: FSSAI license, GST certificate, bank details, PAN\n5. Zomato verification visit (1-3 days)\n6. Go live in 7-14 days\n\n**Tips for better Zomato performance:**\n- Upload high-quality food photos (professional photography pays off)\n- Keep your menu updated ŌĆö remove unavailable items immediately\n- Respond to all reviews within 24 hours\n- Maintain 4.0+ rating to stay in top search results\n- Use Zomato Gold/Pro promotions during launch\n\n### How to Set Up on Swiggy\n\n1. Visit partner.swiggy.com\n2. Similar process to Zomato\n3. Go live in 5-10 days\n\n**Should you be on both?**\nYes, for most restaurants. Zomato and Swiggy have different user bases. Being on both increases your order volume by 40-60% compared to being on just one platform.\n\n## Option 2: Your Own Website Ordering (0% Commission)\n\nThis is where the real money is. Your own ordering page means:\n- 0% commission (vs 20-25% on aggregators)\n- Direct customer relationship\n- Your own customer data\n- No algorithm dependency\n- Full control over promotions\n\n### How to Set Up Your Own Ordering Page\n\n**Option A: Simple WhatsApp Ordering**\nThe simplest approach ŌĆö customers WhatsApp their order, you confirm and deliver. No technology needed. Works well for restaurants with a loyal customer base.\n\n**Option B: Google Business Ordering**\nFree, easy to set up. Customers can order directly from your Google Maps listing. Limited customization but zero cost.\n\n**Option C: Dedicated Ordering Website**\nPlatforms like Dotpe, Thrive, or a custom website. Costs Ōé╣2,000-10,000/month but gives you full control. Best for restaurants doing Ōé╣3+ lakh/month in delivery.\n\n**Option D: BillByteKOT Online Ordering**\nBillByteKOT includes a built-in online ordering page that integrates directly with your KOT and billing system. Orders appear automatically in your kitchen ŌĆö no manual entry.\n\n## Packaging Tips for Delivery\n\nDelivery packaging is your brand ambassador. Bad packaging = bad reviews, even if the food is great.\n\n**Packaging essentials:**\n- **Leak-proof containers:** Especially for gravies and soups\n- **Separate packaging for wet and dry items:** Biryani and raita in separate containers\n- **Tamper-evident seals:** Builds customer trust\n- **Insulated bags:** Keeps food hot for 30-45 minutes\n- **Branded packaging:** Your logo on every container is free marketing\n\n**Packaging cost benchmarks:**\n- Basic packaging: Ōé╣8-15 per order\n- Premium branded packaging: Ōé╣20-35 per order\n- Eco-friendly packaging: Ōé╣15-25 per order\n\nFactor packaging cost into your delivery pricing.\n\n## Managing Online and Dine-In Orders Simultaneously\n\nThis is where most restaurants struggle. When a delivery order comes in during a busy dine-in service, who handles it? How does the kitchen prioritize?\n\n**The problem without a system:**\n- Delivery orders get lost in the chaos\n- Kitchen doesn't know which orders are for delivery vs dine-in\n- Delivery times are missed, leading to bad ratings\n- Staff confusion and errors\n\n**The solution with an integrated POS/KOT system:**\n- All orders (dine-in, delivery, takeaway) appear on the same kitchen display\n- Each order is tagged with its type and priority\n- Kitchen can see all pending orders at once\n- Delivery orders are flagged with estimated pickup time\n\nBillByteKOT handles all order types in one system ŌĆö dine-in KOTs, delivery orders, and takeaway orders all flow through the same kitchen display.\n\n## The Math: When to Go Direct\n\nHere's the calculation that changes how you think about delivery:\n\n**Scenario: Ōé╣5 lakh monthly delivery revenue**\n\n| Channel | Revenue | Commission | You Keep |\n|---------|---------|-----------|----------|\n| 100% Zomato/Swiggy | Ōé╣5,00,000 | Ōé╣1,10,000 (22%) | Ōé╣3,90,000 |\n| 70% Aggregators + 30% Direct | Ōé╣5,00,000 | Ōé╣77,000 (15.4%) | Ōé╣4,23,000 |\n| 50% Aggregators + 50% Direct | Ōé╣5,00,000 | Ōé╣55,000 (11%) | Ōé╣4,45,000 |\n\nShifting just 30% of orders to direct channels saves Ōé╣33,000/month ŌĆö Ōé╣3.96 lakh/year.\n\nThe investment to build a direct ordering channel? Ōé╣5,000-15,000 in setup costs. ROI in under 2 weeks.\n\n**[Set up online ordering with BillByteKOT ŌĆö start your free 7-day trial ŌåÆ](/login?trial=7days)**"
