    relatedPosts: [],
    content: "# Restaurant Profit & Loss Statement: How to Read and Improve Yours\n\nHere's a question that reveals everything about a restaurant's financial health: \"What was your net profit margin last month?\"\n\nMost restaurant owners can't answer this. They know their revenue (roughly). They know their rent. But the full picture ŌĆö where every rupee goes and how much is left ŌĆö is a mystery. **This is why 60% of restaurants fail within 3 years.**\n\nYour Profit & Loss (P&L) statement is the financial X-ray of your restaurant. Here's how to read it and use it to improve your business.\n\n## What a Restaurant P&L Looks Like\n\nHere's a sample P&L for a mid-size casual dining restaurant doing Ōé╣8 lakh/month in revenue:\n\n```\nRESTAURANT P&L STATEMENT ŌĆö March 2026\n\nREVENUE\nFood Sales                          Ōé╣6,80,000\nBeverage Sales                      Ōé╣1,20,000\nTotal Revenue                       Ōé╣8,00,000    100%\n\nCOST OF GOODS SOLD (COGS)\nFood Cost                           Ōé╣2,38,000     29.8%\nBeverage Cost                       Ōé╣36,000        4.5%\nTotal COGS                          Ōé╣2,74,000     34.3%\n\nGROSS PROFIT                        Ōé╣5,26,000     65.7%\n\nOPERATING EXPENSES\nRent                                Ōé╣80,000       10.0%\nStaff Salaries                      Ōé╣1,60,000     20.0%\nUtilities (gas, electricity, water) Ōé╣32,000        4.0%\nMarketing                           Ōé╣16,000        2.0%\nMaintenance and repairs             Ōé╣8,000         1.0%\nPackaging and supplies              Ōé╣12,000        1.5%\nSoftware and subscriptions          Ōé╣2,000         0.3%\nMiscellaneous                       Ōé╣8,000         1.0%\nTotal Operating Expenses            Ōé╣3,18,000     39.8%\n\nEBITDA                              Ōé╣2,08,000     26.0%\n\nDepreciation                        Ōé╣12,000        1.5%\nInterest (if any loans)             Ōé╣8,000         1.0%\nTaxes                               Ōé╣28,000        3.5%\n\nNET PROFIT                          Ōé╣1,60,000     20.0%\n```\n\n## Industry Benchmarks for Each Line Item\n\n| Line Item | Good | Acceptable | Warning |\n|-----------|------|-----------|--------|\n| Food Cost % | 28-32% | 33-38% | 39%+ |\n| Beverage Cost % | 20-30% | 31-35% | 36%+ |\n| Total COGS | 30-35% | 36-40% | 41%+ |\n| Gross Profit | 65-70% | 60-65% | <60% |\n| Rent | 8-12% | 13-15% | 16%+ |\n| Staff Costs | 25-35% | 36-40% | 41%+ |\n| Utilities | 3-5% | 6-8% | 9%+ |\n| EBITDA | 20-30% | 15-20% | <15% |\n| Net Profit | 15-25% | 10-15% | <10% |\n\nCompare your numbers to these benchmarks. Any line item in the \"Warning\" zone needs immediate attention.\n\n## How to Identify Where You're Losing Money\n\n**Step 1: Calculate your percentages**\nFor every line item, divide by total revenue and multiply by 100. This gives you the percentage of revenue that goes to each expense.\n\n**Step 2: Compare to benchmarks**\nWhich line items are above the \"Acceptable\" range? These are your problem areas.\n\n**Step 3: Investigate the outliers**\nIf your food cost is 42% (vs 32% benchmark), dig deeper:\n- Is it a specific category (meat, seafood)?\n- Is it a specific shift (dinner vs lunch)?\n- Is it a specific dish (your biryani might have a 55% food cost)?\n\nYour POS system's item-level sales reports can help you identify which dishes are dragging up your food cost.\n\n## 5 Levers to Improve Your P&L\n\n### Lever 1: Reduce Food Cost (Impact: High)\nEvery 1% reduction in food cost = 1% more net profit. On Ōé╣8 lakh revenue, that's Ōé╣8,000/month. Tactics: FIFO, portion control, supplier negotiation, menu engineering.\n\n### Lever 2: Increase Average Check Size (Impact: High)\nHigher revenue with the same fixed costs = better margins. Tactics: upselling, menu engineering, premium options, combo deals.\n\n### Lever 3: Optimize Staff Costs (Impact: Medium)\nStaff costs are your largest controllable expense after food. Tactics: better scheduling, cross-training, reducing overtime, performance-based incentives.\n\n### Lever 4: Reduce Rent as a % of Revenue (Impact: Medium)\nYou can't reduce rent, but you can increase revenue to make rent a smaller percentage. Alternatively, negotiate rent reduction during slow seasons.\n\n### Lever 5: Reduce Waste and Miscellaneous (Impact: Low-Medium)\nSmall leaks add up. Audit your miscellaneous expenses monthly. What's in there? Are all subscriptions being used? Are utility bills optimized?\n\n## How Daily POS Reports Feed Your Monthly P&L\n\nYour P&L is only as accurate as the data that feeds it. Here's how your POS system connects to your P&L:\n\n- **Daily sales reports** ŌåÆ Monthly revenue figures\n- **Item-level sales** ŌåÆ Food cost analysis by dish\n- **Payment method breakdown** ŌåÆ Cash vs UPI vs card reconciliation\n- **Discount and void reports** ŌåÆ Identifies revenue leakage\n- **Staff performance reports** ŌåÆ Informs staffing decisions\n\nBillByteKOT generates daily, weekly, and monthly reports that give you the data to build an accurate P&L. Restaurant owners using BillByteKOT spend 70% less time on financial reporting.\n\n## Sample P&L Template\n\nDownload and customize this template for your restaurant:\n\n```\nMONTHLY P&L TEMPLATE\n\nREVENUE\nFood Sales:              Ōé╣_______\nBeverage Sales:          Ōé╣_______\nOther Revenue:           Ōé╣_______\nTotal Revenue:           Ōé╣_______  (100%)\n\nCOGS\nFood Cost:               Ōé╣_______  (____%)\nBeverage Cost:           Ōé╣_______  (____%)\nTotal COGS:              Ōé╣_______  (____%)\n\nGROSS PROFIT:            Ōé╣_______  (____%)\n\nOPERATING EXPENSES\nRent:                    Ōé╣_______  (____%)\nStaff Salaries:          Ōé╣_______  (____%)\nUtilities:               Ōé╣_______  (____%)\nMarketing:               Ōé╣_______  (____%)\nMaintenance:             Ōé╣_______  (____%)\nPackaging:               Ōé╣_______  (____%)\nSoftware:                Ōé╣_______  (____%)\nMiscellaneous:           Ōé╣_______  (____%)\nTotal OpEx:              Ōé╣_______  (____%)\n\nEBITDA:                  Ōé╣_______  (____%)\nDepreciation:            Ōé╣_______  (____%)\nInterest:                Ōé╣_______  (____%)\nTaxes:                   Ōé╣_______  (____%)\n\nNET PROFIT:              Ōé╣_______  (____%)\n```\n\n**[Get the daily reports you need to build your P&L ŌĆö start BillByteKOT free for 7 days ŌåÆ](/login?trial=7days)**"
