    content: "# How to Reduce Zomato and Swiggy Commission Costs in 2026\n\nHere's the number that should make every restaurant owner angry: **Zomato and Swiggy collectively earned Ōé╣8,400 crore in commission revenue in 2025**. That money came directly from restaurant owners ŌĆö from your revenue.\n\nThe average restaurant on Zomato/Swiggy pays 20-25% commission. On Ōé╣10 lakh monthly delivery revenue, that's Ōé╣2-2.5 lakh going to aggregators every month. Ōé╣24-30 lakh per year. Enough to hire 3 extra staff, renovate your restaurant, or simply keep as profit.\n\nHere's how to reduce that number ŌĆö without abandoning the platforms entirely.\n\n## How Much Zomato and Swiggy Actually Charge\n\nThe headline commission rate (18-22%) is just the beginning. Here's the full breakdown:\n\n| Fee Type | Zomato | Swiggy |\n|----------|--------|--------|\n| Base commission | 18-22% | 18-22% |\n| Payment gateway fee | 2% | 2% |\n| Packaging fee | Ōé╣5-15/order | Ōé╣5-15/order |\n| Advertising (optional) | Variable | Variable |\n| Priority listing (optional) | Ōé╣5,000-20,000/month | Ōé╣5,000-20,000/month |\n| **Effective rate (without ads)** | **20-25%** | **20-25%** |\n| **Effective rate (with ads)** | **25-35%** | **25-35%** |\n\nRestaurants that run ads on Zomato/Swiggy to maintain visibility are often paying 30-35% effective commission. On Ōé╣10 lakh revenue, that's Ōé╣3-3.5 lakh/month.\n\n## Why Restaurants Are Trapped\n\nThe aggregator trap works like this:\n1. You join Zomato/Swiggy for the customer base\n2. Customers discover you through the platform\n3. You become dependent on the platform for orders\n4. Platform raises commission rates\n5. You can't leave because you'd lose all those customers\n6. You're trapped\n\nThe solution isn't to leave the platforms ŌĆö it's to build parallel channels so you're not dependent on them.\n\n## 7 Strategies to Reduce Aggregator Dependency\n\n### Strategy 1: Build Your Own Ordering Page\n\nThe most impactful strategy. Your own ordering page means 0% commission.\n\n**How to build it:**\n- **Free option:** Google Business ordering (basic but free)\n- **Low-cost option:** Dotpe or similar (Ōé╣1,000-3,000/month)\n- **Full-featured option:** Custom website with ordering (Ōé╣5,000-15,000/month)\n\n**How to drive traffic to it:**\n- Print your ordering URL on every bill\n- Add it to your WhatsApp status\n- Post it on Instagram bio\n- Tell customers directly: \"Order directly from us and save 10%\"\n\n### Strategy 2: WhatsApp Ordering\n\nWhatsApp is India's most-used app. Setting up WhatsApp ordering is free and surprisingly effective.\n\n**How it works:**\n1. Create a WhatsApp Business account\n2. Set up a catalog with your menu items\n3. Customers browse your catalog and send their order\n4. You confirm and arrange delivery\n\nNo commission, direct customer relationship, and customers love the convenience.\n\n### Strategy 3: Loyalty Programs That Drive Direct Orders\n\nOffer a loyalty benefit that's only available for direct orders:\n- \"Order directly and earn double loyalty points\"\n- \"Direct orders get free delivery\"\n- \"10% discount on all direct orders\"\n\nThis gives customers a financial reason to order directly rather than through aggregators.\n\n### Strategy 4: Negotiate Better Rates with Aggregators\n\nMost restaurant owners don't know this: **commission rates are negotiable**, especially for high-volume restaurants.\n\n**How to negotiate:**\n- Track your monthly order volume and revenue on each platform\n- Request a meeting with your account manager\n- Present your volume data and ask for a reduced rate\n- Mention that you're considering reducing your presence on the platform\n- High-volume restaurants (Ōé╣5+ lakh/month) can often negotiate 2-5% reduction\n\nA 2% reduction on Ōé╣10 lakh monthly revenue = Ōé╣20,000/month saved.\n\n### Strategy 5: Optimize Your Aggregator Presence to Reduce Ad Spend\n\nMany restaurants spend Ōé╣10,000-30,000/month on Zomato/Swiggy ads to maintain visibility. You can reduce this by:\n\n- Maintaining a 4.3+ rating (organic ranking improves)\n- Responding to all reviews (algorithm rewards engagement)\n- Keeping your menu updated (fresh menus rank better)\n- Optimizing your menu photos (better photos = higher conversion = better ranking)\n\nA restaurant that improved its rating from 3.8 to 4.4 reduced its ad spend by 60% while maintaining the same order volume.\n\n### Strategy 6: Build a Direct Delivery Capability\n\nAggregators charge partly because they provide delivery. If you build your own delivery capability, you can offer direct ordering with delivery.\n\n**Options:**\n- Hire 1-2 delivery staff (cost: Ōé╣15,000-25,000/month each)\n- Use Dunzo/Porter for on-demand delivery (lower commission than Zomato/Swiggy)\n- Partner with a local delivery service\n\nThis works best for restaurants with a loyal customer base in a defined delivery radius.\n\n### Strategy 7: Focus on Dine-In and Takeaway\n\nThe simplest way to reduce aggregator dependency: grow your dine-in and takeaway revenue. These channels have 0% commission.\n\nEvery Ōé╣1 lakh shift from delivery to dine-in saves Ōé╣20,000-25,000 in commission.\n\n## The Math: When It Makes Sense to Go Direct\n\n**Scenario: Restaurant doing Ōé╣8 lakh/month total, 50% delivery**\n\n| Scenario | Delivery Revenue | Commission | You Keep |\n|----------|-----------------|-----------|----------|\n| 100% aggregators | Ōé╣4,00,000 | Ōé╣88,000 (22%) | Ōé╣3,12,000 |\n| 70% aggregators + 30% direct | Ōé╣4,00,000 | Ōé╣61,600 (15.4%) | Ōé╣3,38,400 |\n| 50% aggregators + 50% direct | Ōé╣4,00,000 | Ōé╣44,000 (11%) | Ōé╣3,56,000 |\n\nShifting 30% of delivery orders to direct channels saves Ōé╣26,400/month ŌĆö Ōé╣3.17 lakh/year.\n\nThe cost to build a direct ordering channel: Ōé╣2,000-5,000/month. ROI: 5-13x.\n\n## Tools to Manage Both Channels\n\nManaging orders from Zomato, Swiggy, and your own ordering page simultaneously requires a system. BillByteKOT integrates all order channels into one dashboard:\n- Zomato and Swiggy orders appear in your KOT system automatically\n- Direct orders from your website/WhatsApp are entered manually or via integration\n- All orders flow through the same kitchen display\n- Consolidated reporting across all channels\n\n**[Manage all your delivery channels with BillByteKOT ŌĆö start your free 7-day trial ŌåÆ](/login?trial=7days)**"
