    content: "# Restaurant Opening Checklist India 2026: 50 Things to Do Before Day 1\n\nEvery year, thousands of restaurants open in India ŌĆö and 60% of them close within 3 years. The most common reason isn't bad food or wrong location. It's **poor preparation**. Missing a license, underestimating costs, hiring the wrong staff, or launching without a billing system ŌĆö these are the mistakes that kill restaurants before they find their footing.\n\nThis 50-item checklist, organized by timeline, ensures you don't miss anything critical.\n\n## 90 Days Before Opening\n\n### Licenses and Legal (Start Early ŌĆö These Take Time)\n\n**1. FSSAI License**\nMandatory for all food businesses. Apply at fssai.gov.in.\n- Basic registration (turnover < Ōé╣12 lakh): Ōé╣100/year\n- State license (Ōé╣12 lakh - Ōé╣20 crore): Ōé╣2,000-5,000/year\n- Processing time: 7-30 days\n\n**2. GST Registration**\nMandatory if annual turnover > Ōé╣20 lakh. Apply at gstin.gov.in.\n- Cost: Free\n- Processing time: 3-7 days\n\n**3. Trade License**\nFrom your local municipal corporation.\n- Cost: Ōé╣500-5,000 (varies by city and size)\n- Processing time: 15-30 days\n\n**4. Fire NOC**\nFrom your local fire department. Required for restaurants above a certain size (varies by state).\n- Cost: Ōé╣1,000-10,000\n- Processing time: 15-45 days\n\n**5. Eating House License**\nFrom local police or municipal authority.\n- Cost: Ōé╣1,000-3,000\n- Processing time: 15-30 days\n\n**6. Liquor License (if applicable)**\nIf you plan to serve alcohol. This is the most complex and expensive license.\n- Cost: Ōé╣50,000-5,00,000+ (varies dramatically by state)\n- Processing time: 30-90 days\n\n**7. Signage Permission**\nFrom municipal corporation for your outdoor signage.\n- Cost: Ōé╣500-5,000/year\n\n**8. Music License**\nIf you play music in your restaurant (PPL and IPRS licenses).\n- Cost: Ōé╣5,000-20,000/year\n\n**9. Weights and Measures License**\nIf you sell items by weight.\n- Cost: Ōé╣500-2,000\n\n**10. Shop and Establishment Registration**\nFrom your state labor department.\n- Cost: Ōé╣500-2,000\n- Processing time: 7-15 days\n\n### Location and Infrastructure\n\n**11. Finalize lease agreement**\nGet a lawyer to review. Ensure the lease allows restaurant use.\n\n**12. Verify utilities**\nConfirm adequate power supply (3-phase for commercial kitchen), water supply, and drainage.\n\n**13. Get structural assessment**\nEnsure the building can handle commercial kitchen equipment weight and ventilation requirements.\n\n**14. Plan kitchen layout**\nWork with a kitchen designer or experienced chef. A well-designed kitchen is 30% more efficient.\n\n**15. Plan dining room layout**\nMaximize covers while maintaining comfort. Aim for 15-18 sq ft per cover for casual dining.\n\n## 60 Days Before Opening\n\n### Equipment\n\n**16. Commercial kitchen equipment**\nGas range, refrigerators, freezers, prep tables, exhaust hood. Budget: Ōé╣1.5-5 lakh depending on size.\n\n**17. Dining room furniture**\nTables, chairs, lighting. Budget: Ōé╣50,000-3 lakh depending on concept.\n\n**18. POS and billing system**\nDon't open without one. BillByteKOT at Ōé╣1,199/year is the most affordable full-featured option.\n\n**19. Thermal receipt printer**\nFor customer bills. Budget: Ōé╣3,000-8,000.\n\n**20. KOT printer for kitchen**\nFor kitchen order tickets. Budget: Ōé╣3,000-8,000.\n\n**21. Cash drawer**\nFor cash management. Budget: Ōé╣1,500-4,000.\n\n**22. Refrigeration for front of house**\nFor beverages and desserts. Budget: Ōé╣15,000-40,000.\n\n**23. Smallwares**\nPlates, glasses, cutlery, serving dishes. Budget: Ōé╣30,000-1 lakh.\n\n**24. Cleaning equipment**\nMops, brooms, cleaning supplies, dishwasher (if applicable).\n\n**25. Safety equipment**\nFire extinguishers, first aid kit, smoke detectors.\n\n### Staff\n\n**26. Hire head chef**\nThe most important hire. Take your time.\n\n**27. Hire kitchen staff**\nLine cooks, prep cooks, dishwashers.\n\n**28. Hire front of house staff**\nWaiters, host, cashier.\n\n**29. Hire manager**\nIf you won't be present full-time.\n\n**30. Set up payroll system**\nBank accounts, salary structure, PF/ESI registration if applicable.\n\n## 30 Days Before Opening\n\n### Menu\n\n**31. Finalize menu**\nTest every dish. Get feedback from trusted people.\n\n**32. Calculate food costs**\nFor every dish. Ensure your pricing gives you 65%+ gross margin.\n\n**33. Design and print menus**\nProfessional design makes a difference. Budget: Ōé╣5,000-20,000.\n\n**34. Set up menu in POS system**\nEnter every item with correct prices and GST rates.\n\n**35. Source all ingredients**\nIdentify and test suppliers for every ingredient.\n\n### Marketing\n\n**36. Create Google Business listing**\nFree and essential. Add photos, hours, menu, and contact details.\n\n**37. Set up Instagram and Facebook**\nStart posting 2 weeks before opening to build anticipation.\n\n**38. List on Zomato and Swiggy**\nStart the onboarding process now ŌĆö it takes 7-14 days.\n\n**39. Create WhatsApp Business account**\nFor customer communication and ordering.\n\n**40. Plan opening day promotion**\nDiscount, free item, or special event to drive initial traffic.\n\n**41. Invite food bloggers and influencers**\nFor a pre-opening tasting. Their posts can drive significant initial traffic.\n\n## 1 Week Before Opening\n\n**42. Staff training**\nComplete the 7-day training plan for all new staff.\n\n**43. Kitchen trial runs**\nCook every menu item multiple times. Time the preparation.\n\n**44. Soft launch**\nInvite friends, family, and trusted customers for a soft launch. Get honest feedback.\n\n**45. Fix issues from soft launch**\nAddress every piece of feedback before the official opening.\n\n**46. Stock inventory**\nOrder enough for the first 2 weeks. Don't over-order ŌĆö you don't know your actual usage yet.\n\n**47. Test all systems**\nPOS, printers, payment terminals, KOT system. Test under load.\n\n**48. Brief all staff**\nFinal briefing on opening day expectations, protocols, and emergency procedures.\n\n## Opening Day\n\n**49. Opening day checklist**\n- All staff present and in uniform\n- Kitchen fully prepped\n- All equipment working\n- POS system running\n- Cash float in place\n- Manager on floor\n\n**50. Document everything**\nTake photos and videos of your opening day. You'll want them for marketing and memories.\n\n## Estimated Costs by Category\n\n| Category | Minimum | Maximum |\n|----------|---------|--------|\n| Licenses | Ōé╣15,000 | Ōé╣50,000 |\n| Kitchen equipment | Ōé╣1,50,000 | Ōé╣8,00,000 |\n| Dining room setup | Ōé╣50,000 | Ōé╣5,00,000 |\n| POS and billing | Ōé╣10,000 | Ōé╣50,000 |\n| Initial inventory | Ōé╣50,000 | Ōé╣2,00,000 |\n| Staff (first month) | Ōé╣1,00,000 | Ōé╣5,00,000 |\n| Marketing | Ōé╣20,000 | Ōé╣1,00,000 |\n| Working capital | Ōé╣2,00,000 | Ōé╣10,00,000 |\n| **Total** | **Ōé╣5,95,000** | **Ōé╣31,50,000** |\n\n**[Set up your restaurant billing system before Day 1 ŌĆö start BillByteKOT free for 7 days ŌåÆ](/login?trial=7days)**"
