    content: "# Restaurant Daily Operations Checklist: Open, Run, and Close Like a Pro\n\nThe best restaurants in the world aren't run on talent alone ŌĆö they're run on **systems**. McDonald's serves 69 million customers per day not because every employee is a culinary genius, but because every process is documented, standardized, and followed consistently.\n\nYour restaurant doesn't need McDonald's complexity. But it does need a daily operations checklist. Here's the complete one.\n\n## Why Checklists Work\n\nA study of hospital operating rooms found that using a simple pre-surgery checklist reduced complications by 36% and deaths by 47%. The same principle applies to restaurants: checklists prevent the \"I thought someone else did it\" failures that cost you customers, money, and reputation.\n\nA restaurant with a daily checklist:\n- Never opens with a broken piece of equipment\n- Never runs out of a key ingredient mid-service\n- Never has a cash discrepancy that takes hours to resolve\n- Never closes with a dirty kitchen that fails a health inspection\n\n## The Opening Checklist (90 Minutes Before Service)\n\n### Kitchen Opening (60 minutes before service)\n\n**Equipment Check:**\n- [ ] Gas lines open and working\n- [ ] All burners igniting properly\n- [ ] Refrigerators at correct temperature (below 4┬░C)\n- [ ] Freezers at correct temperature (below -18┬░C)\n- [ ] Exhaust hood working\n- [ ] Fryers at correct temperature (if applicable)\n- [ ] Dishwasher working and loaded with detergent\n\n**Inventory Check:**\n- [ ] Check all ingredients against today's menu\n- [ ] Identify any items that are low or out of stock\n- [ ] Update 86 list (items unavailable today)\n- [ ] Check expiry dates on all perishables\n- [ ] Verify yesterday's delivery was stored correctly (FIFO)\n\n**Prep Work:**\n- [ ] All mise en place for today's service\n- [ ] Sauces and stocks prepared or reheated\n- [ ] Slow-cooking items started (dal, stocks, slow-cooked meats)\n- [ ] Garnishes prepared\n- [ ] Portion sizes verified\n\n### Front of House Opening (30 minutes before service)\n\n**Dining Room:**\n- [ ] All tables clean and properly set\n- [ ] Menus clean and available (no torn or stained menus)\n- [ ] Condiments stocked and clean\n- [ ] Flowers/decorations fresh (if applicable)\n- [ ] Music playing at appropriate volume\n- [ ] Lighting set correctly\n- [ ] Bathrooms clean and stocked\n\n**POS and Billing:**\n- [ ] POS system logged in and working\n- [ ] Receipt printer loaded with paper\n- [ ] KOT printer loaded with paper\n- [ ] Cash float counted and correct (record opening float amount)\n- [ ] UPI QR codes in place on all tables\n- [ ] Daily specials entered in POS system\n\n**Staff Briefing (15 minutes before service):**\n- [ ] All staff present and in uniform\n- [ ] Today's specials communicated\n- [ ] 86 list communicated\n- [ ] Any special reservations or events noted\n- [ ] One focus area for today's service (\"Let's work on faster billing today\")\n\n## The Mid-Day Checklist (During Service)\n\n### Every 2 Hours:\n- [ ] Check inventory levels of high-usage items\n- [ ] Reorder anything approaching par level\n- [ ] Check bathroom cleanliness\n- [ ] Check dining room cleanliness\n- [ ] Check staff energy levels ŌĆö rotate breaks if needed\n\n### Quality Checks:\n- [ ] Random dish quality check (taste a dish before it goes out)\n- [ ] Check portion sizes are consistent\n- [ ] Check food temperature (hot food hot, cold food cold)\n- [ ] Check presentation standards\n\n### Waste Tracking:\n- [ ] Record any food waste in the daily waste log\n- [ ] Note reasons for waste (spoilage, over-prep, customer return)\n\n### Inventory Reorder:\n- [ ] Place orders for any items that will run out before next delivery\n- [ ] Update 86 list if any items run out\n- [ ] Communicate 86 list updates to all staff immediately\n\n## The Closing Checklist (After Last Customer Leaves)\n\n### Cash Reconciliation:\n- [ ] Count all cash in the drawer\n- [ ] Compare to POS cash sales report\n- [ ] Record any discrepancy (over or under)\n- [ ] Prepare bank deposit\n- [ ] Set tomorrow's opening float\n- [ ] Lock cash in safe\n\n### Inventory Count:\n- [ ] Count all high-value ingredients\n- [ ] Compare to expected levels (opening stock + deliveries - sales)\n- [ ] Record any significant discrepancies\n- [ ] Update inventory system\n\n### Kitchen Closing:\n- [ ] All food stored properly (labeled, covered, correct temperature)\n- [ ] All surfaces cleaned and sanitized\n- [ ] All equipment cleaned (fryers drained, grills scraped)\n- [ ] Floors swept and mopped\n- [ ] Trash emptied\n- [ ] Gas lines closed\n- [ ] Refrigerators and freezers checked (doors sealed)\n\n### Front of House Closing:\n- [ ] All tables cleared and cleaned\n- [ ] Dining room swept and mopped\n- [ ] Bathrooms cleaned\n- [ ] Menus cleaned and stored\n- [ ] Lights off (except security lighting)\n- [ ] Doors locked\n\n### End-of-Day Reports:\n- [ ] Review daily sales report from POS\n- [ ] Note any unusual patterns (unusually high/low sales, specific items)\n- [ ] Review staff performance notes\n- [ ] Prepare tomorrow's prep list\n- [ ] Note any maintenance issues to address\n\n## How to Use Daily Reports to Spot Trends\n\nYour POS system generates daily reports that are goldmines of operational intelligence ŌĆö if you know how to read them.\n\n**Key metrics to review daily:**\n\n| Metric | What It Tells You |\n|--------|------------------|\n| Total revenue vs yesterday | Is today better or worse? Why? |\n| Revenue by hour | When are your peak and slow periods? |\n| Top-selling items | What's working? |\n| Least-selling items | What should you remove or promote? |\n| Average check size | Are staff upselling effectively? |\n| Payment method breakdown | Cash vs UPI vs card trends |\n| Discount and void amounts | Any unusual patterns? |\n| Table turnover rate | How efficiently are you using your space? |\n\n**Weekly trend analysis (15 minutes every Monday):**\n- Compare this week to last week\n- Compare to same week last month\n- Identify any items with declining sales\n- Identify any items with rising sales\n- Note any operational issues that recurred\n\nBillByteKOT generates all these reports automatically. The daily summary report takes 5 minutes to review and gives you everything you need to make informed decisions.\n\n## The Downloadable Checklist Template\n\nPrint this and laminate it for each station:\n\n```\nDAILY OPERATIONS CHECKLIST ŌĆö [Restaurant Name]\nDate: _______  Shift: Opening / Closing\nManager on duty: _______\n\nOPENING\n[ ] Equipment check complete\n[ ] Inventory check complete\n[ ] Prep complete\n[ ] Dining room set\n[ ] POS ready\n[ ] Cash float: Ōé╣_______\n[ ] Staff briefing done\nReady to open: YES / NO\n\nCLOSING\n[ ] Cash reconciled: Ōé╣_______ (over/under: Ōé╣_______)\n[ ] Inventory counted\n[ ] Kitchen cleaned\n[ ] Dining room cleaned\n[ ] End-of-day report reviewed\n[ ] Tomorrow's prep list made\nAll clear: YES / NO\n\nNotes: _______________________\nSignature: ___________________\n```\n\n**[Run your restaurant like a pro with BillByteKOT's daily reports ŌĆö start your free 7-day trial ŌåÆ](/login?trial=7days)**"
